from transformers import AutoModel
import numpy as np
from PIL import Image
import torch
from IPython.display import Image as IImage

# inits Magi model
model = AutoModel.from_pretrained('ragavsachdeva/magi', trust_remote_code=True).cuda()
In [39]:
# converts an image to a numpy array
def read_image_as_np_array(image_path):
    with open(image_path, "rb") as file:
        image = Image.open(file).convert("L").convert("RGB")
        image = np.array(image)
    return image

# inits test image
image_paths = [
    "./images/mickey.jpg",
]
images = [read_image_as_np_array(image) for image in image_paths]
In [41]:
# runs image through Magi model
with torch.no_grad():
    results = model.predict_detections_and_associations(images)
    text_bboxes_for_all_images = [x["texts"] for x in results]
    ocr_results = model.predict_ocr(images, text_bboxes_for_all_images)

# generates analysis image and transcript text
model.visualise_single_image_prediction(images[0], results[0], filename=f"output/analysis.png")
model.generate_transcript_for_single_image(results[0], ocr_results[0], filename=f"output/transcript.txt")

# displays analysis image
i = IImage(filename='./output/analysis.png')
display(i)

# displays transcript
with open('./output/transcript.txt') as f:
    print(f.read())

In [42]:
# extracts panel bounding box data from the results
panels = results[0]['panels']

# goes panel by panel and crops it into a new image
crop_ct = 1
for panel in panels:
    left, top, right, bottom = panel
    bounds = (left, top, right, bottom)
    with open(image_paths[0], "rb") as f:
        image = Image.open(f)
        cropped = image.crop(bounds)
        cropped.save(f"output/crop_{crop_ct}.jpg")
    crop_ct += 1

# displays three of the crops
for i in range(3):
    i = IImage(filename=f"output/crop_{i+1}.jpg")
    display(i)
